Class Name: MusicManager

Package: (if applicable, e.g., utils/audio)
Language: Java

Description:

The MusicManager class handles all audio playback functionality for the Cock Clashers game. It manages background music, sound effects, volume control, and mute functionality. This class abstracts audio handling to provide a consistent and simple interface for playing, stopping, and controlling in-game audio.

Key Features:

Plays background music tracks with optional looping.

Plays sound effects with adjustable volume.

Controls volume and allows muting/unmuting of music.

Ensures the same music track is not restarted unnecessarily.

Runs sound effects on separate threads to avoid interrupting game flow.


Fields:

Field	Type	Description

Clip musicClip	Clip	Stores the currently playing music clip.
FloatControl musicVolumeControl	FloatControl	Controls the volume of the music clip.
boolean isMuted	boolean	Tracks whether the music is muted.
float currentVolume	float	Stores the current volume level (0.0â€“1.0).
String currentTrack	String	Path of the currently playing music track.


